Program: Outlook
Title: 20/03/2012
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00pkc3y
Last Broadcast Date: Wed 21 Mar 2012
The woman who fell from the sky and lived. Juliane Koepcke was travelling on an internal flight over the Peruvian jungle when it was struck by lightning and disintegrated. She fell from over 10,000 feet into the rainforest and was the only survivor.